snippet.textDisplay:
As an Australian I find myself at odds ideologically with both the general population as well as the politicians on all sides on a wider range of issues every month. This latest headline about Novak and Tennis Australia has so fundamentally floored arguments that cannot be supported by any credible corona virus research that has been conducted. The populations main argument is well I had to be vaccinated so he should have to be as well is such a dangerous one. The government inflaming this by saying he is a danger to the community by being un vaccinated is not only medically wrong it is creating fear where fear is not needed. 
Firstly Medically 
1. There is no person anywhere in the world stating that an un vaccinated person is more likely to transmit the disease. 
2. There is admission by both the WHO, CDC and the Vaccine companies that a person who has recovered from COVID is more protected against the virus that a vaccinated person. Furthermore they are holding antibodies against a larger virus range. 
3. The danger NOVAK poses on a society that is currently having 20K cases a day is not even measurable as someone who has natural immunity. Stats simply do not exists to support an argument. 
4. We could also continue to pull apart the response and vaccine dependency and lack of treatment options available to Australians however that is a different debate. 
Then Politically
1. There is no doubt the federal government made this decision by polls. Honestly I have not seen a government kick more own goals that this one. With NSW aside the lack of leadership and fearmongering going on is criminal 
2. We have created a global embarrassment. The fact Border force would not look at his application before he landed as requested by TA shows that we are living in the land of the power hungry unelected official.  A mature and competent government would have provided clear advice to TA for all players and then stood by that advice and those rules. 

Finally lest not forget NOVAK was granted his medical exemption by 2 independent panels of Australian Doctors who looked at his case as part of a blind study. This was done for 27 AO applicants and only 4 passed. Clearly it was not a rigged system. 
Its important to remember while the media called into question the validity of his application and if he lied on it this was not brought forward as a reason for cancellation by the government in either hearing. 

Firstly the government relied on an incorrectly filled out form and was ruled against because of procedural mishandling. A correct decision. 
Secondly the Fed upheld the decision because the appeal was on the basis of the merit of reason for cancellation by the defence. Also a correct decision legally. 
At no time did a court hear argument or pass a ruling on basis of the medical evidence and the validity of the exemption. This is important to note because one would have to assume that had the government done so they would have ultimately called into question the integrity of its own medical officers and practitioner's. 
In my opinion this is where the Defence made a mistake as the argument should have continued to be taken back to the question. What is invalid about his medical exemption?
